post_text: Heavens Table Food Shelf in coordination with Second Harvest Heartland will be providing a free emergency food distribution to the residents of Martin County. This is an effort by the USDA to connect farm-fresh products with families that have a need. The distribution will be on August 11 from 9-11 at the Martin County Fairgrounds. Please enter the grounds at the south entrance by the arena (not the racetrack), exit on the north side of the arena. You will receive 3 boxes. One will be produced, the second will be poultry and pork meat products and the third will be a variety of dairy products. Due to the 3 box load please be aware of a limit of 2 families per car, with a representative of each family in the car. There will be additional products on hand as well. We will collect data on the ages of family members only. This distribution is open to the public and is free to all who attend. Please mark your calendar.

post_text: GHEC will be hosting an informational session about the 2020-21 school year on Wednesday, August 12th at 6:00 PM in the large gymnasium at the school in Granada. Information on the district’s plan for the safe return to school in the fall will be outlined at this meeting, and there will be time for questions to be addressed. Per executive order 20-81 masks will be required to be worn at this event. GHEC’s plans for safely returning to school will be distributed through email, and be available on the district website following this date as well. This event will be live-streamed on the district's Facebook page, and we will attempt to answer questions commented on the live video. If you have any questions in the meantime please don’t hesitate to contact the GHEC main office at (507) 447-2211.

post_text:
Hi Everyone,
GHEC Schools will be honoring our students, athletes and community each Monday night with Monday Night Lights. This event will occur at 8pm each Monday by turning on the GHEC football field lights for 20 minutes to represent the all that has happened in the year 2020, and to recognize the senior class of 2020 during the COVID-19 shutdown.
There have been examples of this done nationally and many Minnesota communities and schools are taking part. Although groups are not allowed to gather, please look for the lights in the GHEC community sky as we show support for our kids and look forward to the time when they can get back to school and practice and play again.
We know how hard this time away from school is for our students and spring activities participants and especially for our seniors.
Go Jaguars!

post_text:
It is a surreal feeling to see our hallways and classrooms empty here at school! We sure miss each of our students and the excitement that they bring to our building. Today our teachers were hard at work preparing for distance learning, while also practicing some social distancing. Our paraprofessionals and bus drivers assisted with delivering meals and providing childcare services, and our custodial staff is busy disinfecting the building.

If your student is in need of breakfast or lunch, we can deliver this to their bus stop free of charge. Please call the school office at (507) 447-2211 to get a copy of the necessary enrollment form. Also, if you are a healthcare (or other qualifying "essential" employee) in need of childcare for a student under the age of 12, please call the school office to enroll your student.

post_text: Our March Madness Final Four competitors were 1st Grade, 4th Grade, 6th Grade and the Seniors. Each class got to participate in a shoot-out. Our younger students had the option to participate in the shoot-out themselves or to recruit some older friends to help. The overall winners of our March Madness PBIS competition were our First Graders!
